<p>In periodic, democats swerve library should be fully supported as I believe it uses WPIlibs SwerveModuleState datatype.</p>","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"posts_count":17,"updated_at":"2023-04-15T19:06:10.769Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":135,"readers_count":134,"score":37.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":434555,"topic_slug":"wheel-rotation-not-in-sync-during-auto-swerve-drive","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/Mechanical-Advantage/AdvantageKit","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - Mechanical-Advantage/AdvantageKit: Monorepo for robot framework and tools","clicks":3}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":58933,"username":"Aedan_Vongsouthi","name":"Aedan Vongsouthi","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/7ba0ec/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":56369,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Making funky products"},"user_suspended":true,"post_url":"/t/wheel-rotation-not-in-sync-during-auto-swerve-drive/434555/11","custom_user_title":"Making funky products","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3190932,"name":"Curt Rozeboom","username":"BlueEpiphone","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/blueepiphone/{size}/197122_2.png","created_at":"2023-04-15T21:37:54.197Z","cooked":"<p>You don’t need advantage kit to use advantage scope. Just log your swerve states to smart dashboard and pull them into the swerve tab in advantage scope.</p>
<p>Also, we occasionally have this issue with our front left module as well and are trying to figure it out. Might have to diagnose more at worlds unfortunately. A roborio reboot fixes it, if needed on the fly.</p>
<p>When it happens, can you check the status light on the turning Sparkmax? Does it change to red or green or stay blue/purple when you try to move? That’s what ours does.  It’s like the Spark just stops greeting commands.</p>
<p>I’m using YAGSL not democat, but the symptom of the lagging turn motor sounds exactly the same. My current theory is related to CAN communication getting ‘bound’ up somehow. When I check my swerve states in advantage, the front left module turning state spins continuously around like it’s trying to catch up but since no commands are going to the motor or controller, it’s unable to get to its desired state. If I can’t figure out a way to fix this, some sort of module disable might be the only bandaid solution.</p>","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"posts_count":17,"updated_at":"2023-04-15T21:37:54.197Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":103,"readers_count":102,"score":55.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":434555,"topic_slug":"wheel-rotation-not-in-sync-during-auto-swerve-drive","display_username":"Curt Rozeboom","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":58933,"username":"Aedan_Vongsouthi","name":"Aedan Vongsouthi","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/7ba0ec/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":32089,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"5010 Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/wheel-rotation-not-in-sync-during-auto-swerve-drive/434555/12","custom_user_title":"5010 Programming Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":